From e7228911f64b3a3a8376e95dc258c845d76cef61 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Mathias Fussenegger <f.mathias@zignar.net>
Date: Tue, 23 Sep 2025 14:04:06 +0200
Subject: [PATCH] Ensure multiple delayed writes are sent in correct order

If a parse or bind fails the pgwire protocol goes into a `ignoreTillSync`
mode.
In that case it used the `writePendingMessages()` variant of the
DelayableWriteChannel which could output messages in a wrong order if
more than 1 delay happened.
